Description.Description: The original speaker IDs in the corpus are only unique within recording locations. That is two different speakers recorded in Bonn and Kiel may have the same ID. Since this causes problems in CMDI, the original speaker ID was augmented by a '_' followed by the first and 5th char of the dialog name, e.g. 'ANS' becomes 'ANS_ga' for the speaker in Kiel and 'ANS_mn' for the speaker in Bonn. The 1st char is necessary since 'k' was used for the locations 'Karlsruhe' and 'Tokyo'. The entry 'PlaceElementarySchool' is free text and may give an impression about the dialect of the speaker. The 'ActorLanguages' was guessed from the recording location assuming that only native speakers were recruited.
